---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ThemeToggle from '../components/ThemeToggle.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What CIHAGO is, what it's for, and where the name comes from."
>
  <article class="page">
    <h1>About CIHAGO</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>CIHAGO</strong> stands for <em>Can I Have A Go</em>.
      It's a small, slow blog about making the future a better place to
      live in &mdash; and an invitation, mostly to the author and
      occasionally to the reader, to actually <em>have a go</em> at things
      rather than just talk about them.
    </p>

    <p>
      The best way to follow along is <a href="/rss.xml">RSS</a> &mdash;
      see <a href="/why-rss/">Why RSS?</a> for the case.
    </p>

    <p>
      Drafts and works-in-progress are
      <a href="https://github.com/7kfn/cihago/tree/main/src/content/blog">available on GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Appearance</h2>
    <p>
      The site follows your browser's light/dark setting by default.
      Override it here if you'd rather pick:
    </p>
    <ThemeToggle />
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
